    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="392"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d392">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">504.418B1/218</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Marriner</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 2242</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-14">October 14,
                            1935</date>.<lb/>[Received October 25.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In continuation of my despatch No. 2179 of
                    September 19, 1935,<note n="12" xml:id="d392fn12">Not printed.</note> I have the
                    honor to report that the Embassy has again made inquiry of the competent
                    official at the Foreign Office concerning the French Government’s attitude
                    toward the Roerich Pact or Convention. The official stated that his Government
                    has further investigated the matter and is less inclined now than was the case
                    last month to give serious consideration to the Pact. He added that the legal
                    advisers of the Foreign Office had expressed the opinion that the Pact is not
                    worthy of serious consideration, at least at the present moment.</p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Theodore Marriner</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
